M|skills|Add one row to relevant brand + surface table:
M|skills|```
M|skills|| [N] | [YYYY-MM-DD] | [primary lever name] | L[1-8] | [ACTIVE / CAPPED] |
M|skills|```
M|skills|Update Cap Status Summary. If count = 3 → mark CAPPED, alert in output.
M|skills|Add one line to the brand's audience psychology section:
M|skills|```
M|skills|[YYYY-MM-DD] Deep psychology note: [what was learned about audience system targeting, layer performance, or archetype fit this ses]
M|skills|```
M|skills|```
M|skills|[YYYY-MM-DD] — STRATEGY_LOG entry written (Deep): [brand] / [surface] / [primary lever] — [outcome: PENDING]
M|skills|```
M|skills|**Condition:** Previous STRATEGY_LOG entry has Results field filled (not PENDING).
M|skills|**Primary delivery:**
M|skills|- gen full proposal from PROPOSAL_TEMPLATE.md
M|skills|- Send via Gmail MCP → Subject: `[Brand] str Proposal — [Date] — Action Required`
M|skills|- Write to Supabase via YVON dashboard
M|skills|**Fallback (if MCP not configured):**
M|skills|- Write proposal to STRATEGY_LOG.md marked `PROPOSAL_PENDING`
M|skills|- Include in next Marcus CEO brief under "Kahneman Proposal Ready"
M|skills|- Alert Stark in ses output: "Proposal ready — MCP unavailable, saved to STRATEGY_LOG"
M|skills|Trigger manually with: `@kahneman results --brand "[name]" --surface "[surface]" --date "[date]"`
M|skills|A proposal is generated and sent when ALL of the following are true:
M|skills|1. A previous str Log entry has Results field filled (not PENDING)
M|skills|2. At least one full cycle has completed (variant ran, results collected)
M|skills|3. Enough data exists to make a directional recommendation
M|skills|**Proposal contains:**
M|skills|- What was run (variant, lever, surface)
M|skills|- What the results showed (numbers + interpretation)
M|skills|- Psychological diagnosis (why it worked or didn't — mechanism level)
M|skills|- Recommended next move with rationale
M|skills|- A/B variants for next cycle (pre-built)
M|skills|- Triple Cap status update
M|skills|- Overall brand perception progress assessment
M|skills|**Proposal delivery:**
M|skills|- Email to Stark via Gmail MCP
M|skills|- Written to YVON Supabase (CEO dashboard view)
M|skills|- Subject line: `[Brand] str Proposal — [Date] — Action Required`
M|skills|When researching brand examples at runtime:
M|skills|**Step 1 — Find the move:**
M|skills|Search for real brand examples relevant to the current task.
M|skills|Prioritize: current (within 18 months), both large AND small brands,
M|skills|fashion and adjacent categories, examples with measurable outcomes.
M|skills|**Step 2 — Extract the mechanism:**
M|skills|What psychological lever did this brand pull?
M|skills|Which of the 8 layers does this activate?
M|skills|Why did it work for this brand at this stage?
M|skills|**Step 3 — Assess transferability:**
M|skills|What would need to be true about our brand for this mechanism to work?
M|skills|Is our brand at the right lifecycle stage?
M|skills|Does our audience share the same psychological profile?
M|skills|Do we have the brand equity required for this lever to activate?
M|skills|**Step 4 — Engineer natively:**
M|skills|Never reference the source brand in output.
M|skills|Extract the mechanism. Apply it in a way that is native to this brand's
M|skills|voice, aesthetic, archetype, and stage.
M|skills|**Step 5 — doc:**
M|skills|Note the source example and extracted mechanism in the ses log
M|skills|for future reference — but keep it internal, not in client-facing output.
M|skills|The same psychological lever cannot be the PRIMARY driver for more than
M|skills|3 consecutive pieces of cnt on the same brand surface.
M|skills|Tracking: `LEVER_TRACKER.md` per brand per surface.
M|skills|**Why:** Audiences adapt. Repeated activation of the same lever produces
M|skills|diminishing psychological returns. By the 4th repetition, the audience
M|skills|has learned to filter it — it becomes invisible. Variety maintains
M|skills|psychological freshness and prevents the brand from becoming predictable.
M|skills|**What counts as same lever:**
M|skills|Same Cialdini principle, same layer, same core mechanism.
M|skills|Evolving execution (different copy, visual, format) does NOT reset the cap.
M|skills|Only switching the PRIMARY lever resets it.
M|skills|**Cap reset:**
M|skills|Using a different primary lever once resets the previous lever's count.
M|skills|**Override condition:**
M|skills|No override. The Triple Cap Rule is absolute.
M|skills|Even if a lever is performing well — after 3 consecutive uses, switch.
M|skills|The goal is long-term brand health, not short-term metric optimization.
M|skills|*Variant B is the full strategic instrument. For fast, high-frequency cnt
M|skills|work — use 01-kahneman.md. When in doubt about which to use:
M|skills|high-stakes or first-time cnt → Variant B.
M|skills|Recurring or quick-turnaround cnt → Variant A.*
M|skills|> Kahneman appends one line here after each deep ses when results are confirmed.
M|skills|> Format: `[YYYY-MM-DD] [brand] [surface] — [layer] [lever] → [worked/failed] — [mechanism note]`
M|skills|> This table becomes the brand's psychological intelligence over time. Never edit manually.
